			"text": "Selkirkia hails from the middle Cambrian into the Lower Ordovician, with fossils found in the Burgess Shale, Canada, Puncoviscana Formation, Argentina, and the Fezouata Formation, Morocco. It is a tubed archaeopriapulidan, usually found buried in the sand, with its proboscis coming out of the opening of the tube in order to feed, and grew up to 6 cm in length."
